Deputy President, David Mabuza is urging South Africans to remain optimistic during this difficult time. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President, David Mabuza is urging South Africans to remain optimistic during this difficult time. Mabuza says this season should be seen as a season of hope. He's also reiterated calls for people to continue practising covid-19 safety protocols. Mabuza says government is working towards tackling job losses.